subject: RE: [junit] Can anyone send me a zip of the JUnit 4.2 sources?
msgSnippet: Why don t you just download the zip from Sourceforge, it contains the sources. Zipping the cvs content would only give you a snopshot of the current junit
messageBody:
Why don't you just download the zip from Sourceforge, it contains the
sources.

Zipping the cvs content would only give you a snopshot of the current
junit developmeht, which *might* not be compatbile to older releases or
the future final release of Junit 4.3 or whatever it os going to be
named.


________________________________

From: junit@yahoogroups.com [mailto:junit@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
Mark Levison
Sent: Wednesday, March 07, 2007 4:36 PM
To: junit@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [junit] Can anyone send me a zip of the JUnit 4.2 sources?



After two days of waiting Sourceforge's CVS access is still down for
junit. I've only a limited window to dedicate to backporting JUnit 4.2
to Java 1.4 - so I would be grateful to anyone who email the sources
as a zip. Email: mlevison@... <mailto:mlevison%40gmail.com> .

Thanks
Mark Levison
